The idea is to split the transmitted power among several antenna elements, separated in space so as to provide coverage over the same area as a single antenna but with reduced total power and improved reliability.  A single antenna radiating at high power is replaced by a group of low-power antennas to cover the same area.  The idea works because less power is wasted in overcoming penetration and shadowing losses, and because a line of sight channel is present more frequently.
